author: SANJAY KHAJURIA
description: Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha issued a stern warning to Pakistan, stating that any future misadventures would result in the destruction of the "terrorist state" by Indian armed forces. He highlighted the bravery displayed during "Operation Sindoor" following the Pahalgam terror attack and vowed to eliminate terrorism from J&K, ensuring equal punishment for terrorists and their supporters.

author: TNN
description: J&K National Conference will not nominate a replacement for MP Mian Altaf Ahmad in the all-party delegations briefing foreign nations about India’s anti-terrorism stance, after Altaf declined due to religious commitments. This decision means NC will have no political representation in any of the seven delegations.
title: Omar’s party goes unrepresented as party MP opts out of outreach trip

author: OMER FAROOQ
description: Pakistan's 18% defence budget increase to over Rs 2.5 lakh crore amid economic struggles and tensions with India raises concerns about fiscal priorities. Economists fear this move, coupled with costly projects like the Diamer-Bhasha Dam, could jeopardize economic reforms and social spending, especially with a high debt-to-GDP ratio and IMF pressures.
title: Pak’s defence budget hike sparks fiscal priorities debate amid cash crunch

author: SRISHTI LAKHOTIA
description: Calcutta High Court has firmly stated that pension is a legal entitlement, not charity, rebuking Hooghly Chinsurah municipality for delaying pension payments to 148 retired Group D workers, citing technological issues. The court emphasized that delaying pension, earned through years of service, causes undue hardship and violates principles of equity and justice.

author: SANJAY KHAJURIA
description: Jammu & Kashmir police have solved a murder case in Udhampur district, arresting three individuals, including the victim's wife. The investigation began after a decomposed body was discovered in a bag near Laddha village. Authorities identified the deceased as Ravi Kumar, and the suspects confessed to the crime, attributing it to a domestic dispute; the murder weapon has been recovered.

author: TNN
description: Angad Singh Chandok, an alleged economic offender, was apprehended by the CBI at Delhi airport following his deportation from the US. He faced charges in both countries and was taken into custody upon arrival.

author: SIDHARTHA
description: The Indian government is actively working to maintain strong FDI inflows by streamlining regulations and offering tailored investment packages to global corporations. Efforts include easing regulatory frameworks at the state level, simplifying sectoral FDI regulations, and addressing investor concerns regarding land availability.
title: Centre seeks to ensure FDI inflow remains strong

author: TNN
description: A Delhi court has granted the National Investigation Agency (NIA) 15-day custody of a CRPF jawan arrested for espionage. The jawan is accused of leaking sensitive information to Pakistani intelligence officers in exchange for money.
title: Court allows NIA to take custody of CRPF jawan in espionage case

author: RAJAT PANDIT
description: The US Defence Intelligence Agency reports Pakistan views India as an "existential threat," modernizing its military and tactical nuclear weapons to counter India's conventional advantage. India considers China its primary adversary, managing Pakistan as a secondary concern despite recent border skirmishes.

description: In a village near Indore, a 45-year-old tribal woman died after a brutal gangrape and assault. She was found unconscious with severe internal injuries after returning from a wedding with Hari Palvi, who, along with Sunil Korku, is now arrested. The woman reportedly identified her attackers before succumbing to her injuries, which included fatal damage from a sharp object.

description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov is slated to visit India next month, paving the way for President Vladimir Putin's anticipated trip later this year for the annual India-Russia summit. Discussions will likely encompass defense, energy security, and boosting bilateral trade to $100 billion by 2030 using national currencies. NSA Ajit Doval will also attend a security meeting in Moscow.

author: TNN
description: Prime Minister Modi asserted that caste enumeration aims to integrate marginalized communities into the development mainstream, clarifying that the NDA government prioritizes empowerment over caste-based politics. The NDA lauded the caste census initiative, emphasizing its necessity for societal inclusion.

author: PTI
description: In Rajasthan's Karauli, women have spearheaded a remarkable transformation, combating drought and dacoity. Facing declining rainfall and barren lands, they convinced their husbands to abandon crime and revive traditional water bodies. Through community efforts and the support of Tarun Bharat Sangh, they built ponds, revitalized the Serni river, and brought prosperity back to the region, fostering stability and hope.

author: TNN
description: Indian astronaut-designate Shubhanshu Shukla and his three crewmates are entering quarantine as preparations intensify for the Axiom Mission-4 (Ax-4) launch, scheduled for June 8. A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket will carry the crew to the International Space Station for a 14-day mission focused on science, outreach, and commercial activities.

author: SUDHA NAMBUDIRI
description: The sinking of the MSC ELSA 3 container ship off Kochi poses a significant ecological threat to marine and coastal ecosystems, particularly fisheries. author: TNN
description: The southwest monsoon made an early arrival in Goa on Sunday, May 26th, marking the earliest onset in 20 years, according to the IMD. An orange alert has been issued, forecasting heavy to very heavy rainfall and strong winds in the coming days.

author: RICHA PINTO
description: Mumbai is bracing for a potentially record-breaking early monsoon, with the IMD forecasting onset within three days, possibly surpassing the 1956 record of May 29. The southwest monsoon has already reached Devgad, Konkan, ten days ahead of schedule. Favorable conditions suggest further advancement across Maharashtra, including Mumbai.

description: Tej Pratap Yadav, Lalu Prasad's elder son, has become a political liability for the RJD. His erratic behavior and public personal dramas, including a tumultuous marriage and divorce, have overshadowed party agendas.

author: SAIBAL SEN
description: In a Kolkata gang-rape case from May 2003, which went to trial in January 2025, two accused individuals were acquitted due to a lack of evidence and the complainant's inability to recall the incident after two decades.
